  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6 and boil a kettle</p><p>Rinse your <strong>sushi rice </strong>in a sieve under <strong>cold running water</strong> for 30 secs (use your hands to really wash the grains!), then set aside to drain fully</p><p>Add the <strong>sushi rice </strong>to<strong> </strong>an <strong>oven-proof dish </strong>with 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[375ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Cover tightly with<strong> tin foil </strong>and put the dish in the oven for 25 min or until all the water is absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once cooked, transfer the <strong>rice</strong> to a plate and set aside for 10 min or until the rice is cooled</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1697453789233-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
